# ST0021/

Session analysis tool for Claude Code projects. Combines an Elixir preprocessor (autopsy.exs) for JSONL mining with a Claude skill (intent-autopsy) for forensic analysis. Identifies memory gaps, rule violations, capability regressions, and stale memory entries to close the feedback loop.

## Files

- `info.md` -- Steel thread metadata, objective, scope, and deliverables
- `design.md` -- Architecture, data flow, analysis categories, and design decisions
- `impl.md` -- Implementation details, Elixir modules, session format, and technical solutions
- `reference.md` -- User-facing forensic analysis skill with procedures and voice guidelines
- `tasks.md` -- Task dependencies and work package organization
- `done.md` -- Completion status and deliverable checklist
